{
  "texts": [
    "Tracking consists of inferring one or more objects' motion in a sequence of frames (Smeulders et al. 2014).",
    "It is, therefore, inherently related to video analysis, contrary to object detection.",
    "The main tracking approaches can be categorised as single-and multi-object tracking according to the number of objects that should be tracked.",
    "This task is very useful for several surveillance applications, such as traffic monitoring and pedestrian behaviour analysis (see Sect. 3.4).",
    "As mentioned before, some tracking methods exploit instance detection as a sub-task (Sun et al. 2021): in this case, their effectiveness also depends on detection accuracy."
  ]
}